All Classes

Class Description
Bullet
The bullet class provides logic for the player bullet.
EnemyShip
The enemy ship class extended the Ship class.
GameView
The GameView program provides the main player controls, game logic, and visuals for the "Battle X Armada" arcade-shooter-style game.
PlayerShip
Player ship class extends the Ship class.
Server
This program is a server used to send and receive data from the Client (GameView) pertaining to User objects.
Ship
Ship is a super class that defines the coordinates and speed of the player and enemy ships.
Starter
Create the window used to start the game.
User  
User
This User class defines the User Entities which fill the database holding user profiles for our game.
UserProfileRequest
This class is used by the client to send profile requests to the server.
UserProfileResponse
This class is used by the server to send profile responses to the client.
UserRepository
This interface defines the main search methods used by the server to search the database.
UserScoreRequest
This class is used by the client to send score requests to the server.
UserScoreResponse
This class is used by the server to send score responses to the client.
